<Layout title="All Reviews - AI Website Builders">

  <!-- WebPage Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="WebPage"
    data={{
      name: 'All Reviews - AI Website Builders',
      description: 'Complete index of all AI website builder reviews. Hands-on testing of Framer, Durable, 10Web, Relume, and more.',
      url: 'https://vcelyy.github.io/ai-website-builders/reviews'
    }}
  />

  <!-- FAQ Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="FAQPage"
    data={[
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How are AI website builders reviewed?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Each builder is tested hands-on for 20-40 hours. I test generation quality, customization options, actual site launch, code export capabilities, and long-term usability. I build real sites, not demo pages. Example: for e-commerce testing, I built a pet supply store with 24 products, not a placeholder 'Lorem ipsum' site. Reviews are based on real usage, not marketing claims. Total testing investment: 127+ hours across 27 builders."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which AI website builder has the highest score?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Framer has the highest score at 9.3/10, followed by Relume (8.9/10), 10Web (8.8/10), and Webflow (8.7/10). Scores reflect real-world performance across four categories: design quality (40%), features (30%), ease of use (20%), value for money (10%). Framer wins because it generates beautiful designs fast, publishes at PageSpeed 95+, and scales from simple landing pages to complex sites. No builder is perfect, but Framer is closest for most users."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Are these reviews unbiased?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, with full transparency: affiliate links are used (clearly disclosed on every review), but I don't hesitate to call out problems. Example: Durable AI review praises 30-second generation but criticizes 2-hour cleanup time. 10Web review recommends WooCommerce power but warns about WordPress learning curve. Wix review notes beginner-friendliness but calls out generic designs and PageSpeed 62. Review scores reflect real testing results, including lock-in issues, design limitations, and performance problems. I'd rather lose affiliate commission than recommend wrong tool."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How often are reviews updated?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Monthly re-testing of top 10 builders. Quarterly updates for all 27. AI tools change fast‚Äîfeatures added overnight, prices raised without warning, quality drops after updates. Example: Framer AI was mediocre (7.5/10) in 2023, added major features in 2024, now top recommendation (9.3/10). Wix raised prices from $16 to $27/month in 2025‚Äîreview updated within 48 hours. New builder launches? Tested within 2 weeks, added if good enough. Last full site update: January 2026. Outdated reviews waste everyone's time‚Äîpreventing that is priority."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What's the difference between 8.8 and 9.3 scores?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "More than you'd think. 9.3 (Framer): exceptional design quality, fast performance, scales to complex sites. 8.8 (10Web): excellent for specific use case (e-commerce, WordPress), weaker elsewhere. The 0.5 gap represents the difference between 'works beautifully for most people' and 'perfect for specific situations.' Example: if you need e-commerce, 10Web (8.8) beats Framer (9.3) because WooCommerce power matters more than raw design score. Scores guide, not dictate. Always read the full review‚Äîyour situation might value different things."
        }
      },
