        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do you accept payment for positive reviews?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "No. Never happened, never will. I'm offered review fees monthly (usually $200-500 per 'positive review'). All declined. Here's why: one paid review kills credibility forever. If I sell 9.5/10 to Builder X, then Builder Y offers $500 for same, how do I refuse? Once you sell, you're owned. Affiliate model is better: I earn commission when readers sign up, regardless of score. Example: Wix review (8.2/10) generates significant affiliate revenue despite mediocre score‚Äîbecause readers trust the assessment and choose Wix anyway for specific needs. Honest reviews = long-term income. Paid shilling = short-term cash, dead reputation."
        }
